<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Many of the deeper records of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Costa" baseAuthorityYear="1851" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheirus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheirus hopei" order="Amphipoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hopei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Scopelocheirus hopei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, particularly those from the Mediterranean may actually be misidentifications of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bellan-Santini" authorityYear="1985" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheirus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheirus polymedus" order="Amphipoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polymedus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Scopelocheirus polymedus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and should be re-examined to confirm their identity.
</paragraph>
